"title": "8258: fruitfulness, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8258",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Fruitfulness is used by Scripture as a symbol of spiritual maturity and well-being.</p>\n<h2>Spiritual fruitfulness described</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>The results of the Holy Spirit's activity in the life of a Christian believer.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:12\">PSA 92:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:30\">PRO 11:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:17\">ISA 32:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:16\">JER 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10\">EZK 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:9\">EPH 5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:17\">JAS 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual fruitfulness expected in God's people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:2\">ISA 5:1–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:16-Matt7:20\">MAT 7:16–7:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:43-Luke6:44\">LUK 6:43–6:44</a> <em>Such fruitfuless, seen in a person's behaviour, is evidence of their true character</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:4\">ROM 7:4</a></p>\n<h2>The conditions for spiritual fruitfulness</h2>\n<h3>Spiritual fruitfulness through an intimate relationship with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4-John15:5\">JHN 15:4–15:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Spiritual fruitfulness through a commitment to God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1-Ps1:3\">PSA 1:1–1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:23\">MAT 13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:2-John15:3\">JHN 15:2–15:3</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual fruitfulness through a death to self-interest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:24\">JHN 12:24</a></strong> <em>Although Jesus Christ is speaking here primarily of his own death, the principle remains true for Christian living.</em></p>",
